---
description: Security rules for the entire OpenNG codebase
globs: **/*.ts
---

Security is embedded in every layer of OpenNG. Apply these rules to every code change.

## Input Validation
- Validate ALL external input (query params, headers, bodies, URL params) with Zod before use
- Reject unexpected fields — never spread raw request bodies into DB queries or function args
- Validate string length, numeric range, and enum membership — not just type
- Sanitize and validate redirect URLs against APP_URL allowlist

## Secrets
- Hash API keys, magic link tokens, and session tokens with SHA-256 before storing
- Never persist plaintext secrets — show raw keys/tokens to the user exactly once
- All secrets come from environment variables — never hardcode
- Use pino redaction to prevent tokens, keys, passwords, emails, and session IDs from appearing in logs

## Auth Security
- Magic link tokens: 15-minute expiry, single-use (mark used_at on verification)
- Session cookies: HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Lax — never readable by client JS
- Sessions: 30-day sliding expiry — refresh on activity, delete on logout
- Auth failure messages must be generic ("Invalid or expired token") — never reveal whether an email exists or a key is valid vs revoked

## Error Handling
- Never expose stack traces, SQL errors, file paths, or server versions in responses
- All errors use the standard { success: false, error: { code, message, docs } } envelope
- Log technical details internally with logger.error — return a safe message to the client

## Rate Limiting
- Rate-limit auth endpoints aggressively (5 magic link requests per email per hour)
- Anonymous requests limited by IP; authenticated by API key hash
- Always return X-RateLimit-Limit, X-RateLimit-Remaining, X-RateLimit-Reset headers

## CORS
- Allow all origins for GET on /v1/* (public data API)
- Restrict /auth/* and /dashboard/* to APP_URL origin only

## SQL Injection
- All queries go through Drizzle ORM parameterized query builder
- Never concatenate user input into SQL strings
- Stored procedures use parameterized inputs exclusively
